original_definition: 'Liquid-immersed transformer' means a power transformer in which the magnetic circuit and windings are immersed in liquid.
generated_definition: 'Liquid-immersed transformer' means a transformer in which the windings are immersed in a liquid, such as oil or transformer oil, for cooling and insulation purposes.

Article 2: ‘Liquid-immersed transformer’ means a power transformer in which the magnetic circuit and windings are immersed in liquid.
